Ihuoma Chiedozie, Abuja The Federation Accounts Allocation Committee on Thursday shared a total of N769.52bn to the three tiers of government for the month of July 2019. The amount was shared at a meeting which held at the headquarters of the Ministry of Finance in Abuja. The N769.523bn comprised revenue from Value Added Tax, Exchange Gain and Gross Statutory Revenue. A communiqu√© issued at the end of FAAC meeting confirmed that from the total revenue of N769.523bn the Federal Government received N299.8bn, the states got N190.38bn and the Local Government Councils received N143.57bn. The oil producing states received N42.92bn as 13 per cent derivation revenue and the revenue generating agencies got N92.86bn as cost of revenue collection. A breakdown of the distribution showed that from the gross statutory revenue of N674.37bn, the Federal Government received N285.77bn, the states received N144.95bn, and the Local Government Councils received N111.75bn. The oil producing states received N42.816bn as 13 per cent derivation revenue while the revenue collecting agencies received N89.09bn as cost of collection. From the N94.159bn VAT revenue, the Federal Government received N13. 559bn, the states got N45.197bn, the Local Government Councils received N31.638bn and the revenue generating agencies received N3.766bn. At the meeting, the FAAC announced that as at August 22, 2019, the balance in the Excess Crude Account was $274.41m. Figures released by the committee shows that the gross statutory revenue for the month of July 2019 was N674.37bn. The amount was higher than the N652.95bn received in June by N21.42bn Copyright PUNCH.
